******
[2] Feline
Date: Thu 8 Mar 2018
Source: Statens Veterinarmedicinska Anstalt (Sweden State Veterinary Office) [in Swedish, machine trans., edited]
http://sva.se/om-sva/pressrum/nyheter-fran-sva/over-tusen-katter-smittade-av-salmonella


The State Veterinary Office (SVA) has detected 1007 cases of salmonella in cats in just over 2 months since the beginning of 2018. Never before, even in a whole year, so many cats have been found to have salmonellosis in Sweden. Finally, fewer cats are now suffering from this disease.

2018 differs from previous years in 2 ways: partly because the observed cases are so many, partly because the proportion of _Salmonella_ positive samples is so high among the suspected samples obtained. Now, however, "the culmination seems to be reached for this contagion season", said Elina Lahti, epidemiologist at SVA.

Because the cats have the same subtypes of salmonella that birds carry, the cats are infected by birds, for example around the popular areas where birds are fed.

--
